definition: to fill or stuff/(of a form etc) to fill in
earth/dust/clay/local/indigenous/crude opium/unsophisticated/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]
to fill in a form/to write data in a box (on a questionnaire or web form)
to fill a gap/to fill in a blank (on a form)/to overcome a deficiency
to compose a poem (to a given tune)
to fill a job vacancy/to fill in a blank (e.g. on questionnaire or exam paper)
righteous indignation fills one's breast (idiom); to feel indignant at injustice
to fill (gap, hole, area, blank)/to pad out/to complement/(dental) filling/filled

sentences.english: Fill in the blanks with articles if necessary.
sentences.chinese: 在有必要的地方填冠詞。

sentences.english: Would you mind filling in this inquiry form?
sentences.chinese: 請填一下這張意見表好嗎？

sentences.english: Would you fill out the registration form, please?
sentences.chinese: 請您填一下住宿登記表號嗎？

sentences.english: These tax forms are driving me nuts .
sentences.chinese: 填這些納稅申報表快讓我發瘋了。

sentences.english: You need to fill out an application and have your official copy of school transcripts sent to them.
sentences.chinese: 你需要填一張申請表，並送交一份學校的有效證件。

sentences.english: You must fill out this order form.
sentences.chinese: 這個訂貨單你要填一下。

sentences.english: Label each picture the appropriate style of cooking potatoes.
sentences.chinese: 請把正確的土豆烹飪方法填到相應的圖片下方。

sentences.english: Sherbet lemons are hard candies filled with dry sherbet powder.
sentences.chinese: 檸檬果子露其實就是中心填了這種乾果子露粉的硬糖。

sentences.english: Please write the age of your nominee.
sentences.chinese: 請在下面填上被提名者的年齡。

sentences.english: After buying the product, you need to fill out the rebate form.
sentences.chinese: 買了商品後，你得填一個返款表格。

sentences.english: Whatever it was,fill in your favorite blank, fill in the blank in your favorite way.
sentences.chinese: 這裏你可以填上，你最喜歡的任何答案。

sentences.english: Ad valorem stamp duty is payable by the transferee(s) if this form is completed.
sentences.chinese: 如已填妥本表格，承讓人須繳付從價印花稅。

sentences.english: You'll just keep cramming food into yourself until you've eaten too much .
sentences.chinese: 你只是在不停地往嘴裏填東西，直到你喫得胃脹。

sentences.english: I filled out all the necessary forms.
sentences.chinese: 我填了所有必填的表格。

sentences.english: We use diamond-shaped boxes for questions.
sentences.chinese: 所提的問題填在菱形框裏。

sentences.english: NO06, Please fill out this loan-application form.
